The paper proposes methodologies to train deep convolutional neural networks for image super resolution, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of cascade training and network trimming, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark image datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
